From 87983eb00a1b5172afdb31036fa1616413e20315 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthias Petermann <mp@petermann-it.de>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 02:35:24 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Introduce complete NetBSD Cells (3rd generation) stack into
 netbsd-11

Import the full NetBSD Cells stack into the netbsd-11 branch as a
new subsystem, including kernel isolation, runtime control, declarative
orchestration, and interactive operations tooling.

Introduce secmodel_cell as a dedicated kernel security model for cell-aware
authorization and isolation, with membership/accounting plumbing, policy
integration, module/sysctl wiring, and the kernel interfaces required by
userland control tools.

Add cellctl as the low-level runtime control utility that bridges userland
operations to secmodel_cell and provides lifecycle/state/stat control for
cell instances.

Add the cellman control plane and shared libcellman APIs:
declarative desired state in /etc/cellman/*.lua, deterministic typed DSL
loading, explicit apply-based reconciliation, dependency ordering, and
hash-based drift tracking (manifest/service/policy/apply) for predictable
convergence.

Provide stable read/output contracts for automation via --view, -o, -T, and
-H, and include operational workflows for bootstrap, lifecycle/autostart,
mounts/volumes, apply plan execution, backup/restore, and reset/orphan
cleanup.

Enforce fail-closed safety defaults across parser and backend layers,
including strict name/path validation, mount target/overlap guards,
host-path mount opt-in via CELL_ALLOW_HOST_MOUNTS=YES, and explicit --yes
confirmation for destructive operations.

Integrate cellui as the curses frontend over libcellman APIs and add base
system integration artifacts (rc.d scripts, defaults/config files,
mtree/set-list entries, manpages, examples, and documentation under
doc/specs/cells).
