+.Dd March 13, 2026
+.Dt SECMODEL_CELL 9
+.Os
+.Sh NAME
+.Nm secmodel_cell
+.Nd cell security model with kauth isolation and snapshot telemetry
+.Sh DESCRIPTION
+.Nm
+implements a cell-oriented security model on top of
+.Xr kauth 9 .
+Processes are associated with a cell identifier stored in credential-specific
+state.
+Host root
+.Pq effective uid 0 in cell id 0
+is privileged to manage cell membership and cell definitions.
+.Pp
+The model creates and manages entries under
+.Xr sysctl 7
+in
+.Dv security.models.cell .
+These controls are intended for host-root administration.
+.Sh SYSCTL INTERFACE
+The following nodes are created under
+.Dv security.models.cell :
+.Bl -tag -width create
+.It Va id
+Read the current process cell id, or write a cell id to request entry to that
+cell.
+.It Va create
+Create a new cell id.
+The write side accepts a
+.Vt struct cell_create
+request only.
+Callers provide cell metadata and optional settings, including:
+.Bl -tag -width CELL_CREATE_PROFILE
+.It Dv CELL_CREATE_PROFILE
+Select one of the supported policy profiles
+.Pq low, medium, high .
+.It Dv CELL_CREATE_PORTS
+Reserve one or more listening ports for this cell.
+When at least one cell reserves a port, bind attempts for that port are
+allowed only from members of the cell that reserved it.
+.It Dv CELL_CREATE_RLIMIT_NOFILE
+Store an optional supervise-time
+.Dv RLIMIT_NOFILE
+value for this cell.
+.It Dv CELL_CREATE_RLIMIT_AS
+Store an optional supervise-time
+.Dv RLIMIT_AS
+value for this cell.
+.It Dv CELL_CREATE_RLIMIT_CORE
+Store an optional supervise-time
+.Dv RLIMIT_CORE
+value for this cell.
+.El
+.It Va destroy
+Destroy a cell id that has no remaining process members.
+.It Va list
+Read-only array of
+.Vt struct cell_info
+entries for active cells
+.Pq id, name, root, references, process count, sampled CPU windows, sampled virtual-memory size, and optional supervise rlimit metadata .
+Access is restricted to host credentials
+.Pq cell id 0 ,
+including unprivileged host users.
+Access from non-host cells is denied, including cell-local root.
+.El
+.Sh SNAPSHOT METRICS DESIGN
+.Nm
+exports periodic snapshot metrics per cell
+.Pq process count, membership references, sampled virtual-memory size, and CPU tick window metrics .
+These metrics are observation-only and are intended for operational reporting
+via userland tools such as
+.Xr cellctl 8 .
+All values are gauge-style snapshots.
+CPU metrics are exported as per-second deltas plus a rolling 10-second
+average, both derived from sampled process tick counters.
+.Sh OPERATIONAL LOGGING
+.Nm
+emits concise kernel log entries for high-value lifecycle events:
+module load/unload and successful cell create/destroy operations.
+These messages are intended to help administrators correlate policy and
+management actions during incident analysis without excessive noise.
+.Sh SEE ALSO
+.Xr kauth 9 ,
+.Xr secmodel 9 ,
+.Xr secmodel_bsd44 9 ,
+.Xr secmodel_extensions 9 ,
+.Xr secmodel_overlay 9 ,
+.Xr secmodel_securelevel 9 ,
+.Xr secmodel_suser 9 ,
+.Xr sysctl 7
+.Sh HISTORY
+The
+.Nm
+security model first appeared in an unofficial patch set for
+.Nx
+11.0 .
+.Sh AUTHORS
+.An Matthias Petermann Aq Mt mp@petermann-digital.de
