+.Dd March 13, 2026
+.Dt CELLCTL 8
+.Os
+.Sh NAME
+.Nm cellctl
+.Nd manage secmodel cell instances
+.Sh SYNOPSIS
+.Nm
+.Cm create
+.Op Fl l Ar profile
+.Op Fl r Ar port[,port...]
+.Op Fl N Ar nofile|unlimited
+.Op Fl A Ar as|unlimited
+.Op Fl C Ar core|unlimited
+.Fl n Ar name
+.Ar root
+.Nm
+.Cm supervise
+.Op Fl f Ar facility
+.Op Fl o Ar stdout-level
+.Op Fl e Ar stderr-level
+.Op Fl t Ar tag
+.Op Fl U Ar uid
+.Op Fl G Ar gid
+.Op Fl g Ar gid[,gid...]
+.Ar cell-id | name
+.Ar command
+.Op Ar args ...
+.Nm
+.Cm destroy
+.Ar cell-id | name
+.Nm
+.Cm exec
+.Ar cell-id | name
+.Op command
+.Op Ar args ...
+.Nm
+.Cm list
+.Op Fl T
+.Op Fl H
+.Nm
+.Cm stats
+.Op Fl P
+.Op Fl v
+.Op Fl h
+.Op Fl T
+.Op Fl H
+.Sh DESCRIPTION
+The
+.Nm
+utility manages cells provided by the secmodel cell security model.
+Cells are process groups identified by a cell id.
+Processes in a cell can only signal or see other processes with the same
+cell id, while the host root user (cell id 0) can access all processes.
+Read-only listing commands
+.Pq Cm list and Cm stats
+do not modify kernel state and are available to host users
+.Pq cell id 0
+without root privileges.
+These commands are denied to processes running inside non-host cells,
+including cell-local root.
+.Pp
+Cell names must match
+.Dq [A-Za-z0-9._-]
+and are validated by
+.Nm .
+When a command accepts
+.Ar cell-id | name ,
+non-numeric targets must satisfy this name format.
+.Pp
+The commands are as follows:
+.Bl -tag -width Ds
+.It Cm create Op Fl l Ar profile Op Fl r Ar port[,port...] Op Fl N Ar nofile|unlimited Op Fl A Ar as|unlimited Op Fl C Ar core|unlimited Fl n Ar name Ar root
+Create a new cell id, assign it the unique
+.Ar name ,
+and store cell name and root metadata in the kernel cell model.
+This command only creates the cell and prints the resulting cell id.
+.Pp
+The optional flags set isolation policy at creation time.
+.Bl -tag -width Ds
+.It Fl l Ar profile
+Select the cell security profile.
+Valid values are
+.Dq low ,
+.Dq medium ,
+and
+.Dq high .
+The default is
+.Dq high .
+.It Fl r Ar port[,port...]
+Reserve one or more listening ports for this cell.
+.It Fl N Ar nofile|unlimited
+Set
+.Dv RLIMIT_NOFILE
+for supervised processes in this cell.
+.It Fl A Ar as|unlimited
+Set
+.Dv RLIMIT_AS
+for supervised processes in this cell.
+.It Fl C Ar core|unlimited
+Set
+.Dv RLIMIT_CORE
+for supervised processes in this cell.
+.El
+.Pp
+If these rlimit flags are omitted, supervised commands keep the host default
+limit behavior.
+.It Cm supervise Op Fl f Ar facility Op Fl o Ar stdout-level Op Fl e Ar stderr-level Op Fl t Ar tag Op Fl U Ar uid Op Fl G Ar gid Op Fl g Ar gid[,gid...] Ar cell-id | name Ar command Op Ar args ...
+Start a command in an existing cell selected by
+.Ar cell-id
+or
+.Ar name .
+The started command's standard output and standard error are forwarded to
+host syslog by a background supervisor process.
+The
+.Cm supervise
+command daemonizes itself, so callers do not need to wrap it with
+.Xr nohup 1
+or run it in the shell background.
+When create-time rlimits are configured via
+.Cm create
+.Pq Fl N , Fl A , Fl C ,
+the supervisor applies them to each child before executing the target command.
+If the supervised command exits unexpectedly, the supervisor logs the failure
+and restarts it with an exponential backoff delay (capped at 10 seconds).
+.Pp
+The optional flags control supervisor logging:
+.Bl -tag -width Ds
+.It Fl f Ar facility
+Set the syslog facility used by the supervisor and for forwarded
+standard-output and standard-error lines.
+The default is
+.Dq daemon .
+.It Fl o Ar stdout-level
+Set the syslog level used for forwarded standard output lines.
+The level may be specified as one of
+.Dq emerg ,
+.Dq alert ,
+.Dq crit ,
+.Dq err ,
+.Dq warning ,
+.Dq notice ,
+.Dq info ,
+or
+.Dq debug ,
+or as a numeric level from 0 to 7.
+The default is
+.Dq notice .
+.It Fl e Ar stderr-level
+Set the syslog level used for forwarded standard error lines.
+The same values as
+.Fl o
+are accepted.
+The default is
+.Dq err .
+.It Fl t Ar tag
+Set the syslog tag used for forwarded celled-command output.
+If omitted,
+.Dq cellctl
+is used.
+.It Fl U Ar uid
+Drop supervised child credentials to this numeric user id after
+.Xr chroot 2
+and
+the cell membership switch has completed.
+.It Fl G Ar gid
+Drop supervised child credentials to this numeric primary group id.
+When
+.Fl U
+is used,
+.Fl G
+is required, and vice versa.
+.It Fl g Ar gid[,gid...]
+Set supplementary groups for supervised children.
+This option requires
+.Fl U
+and
+.Fl G .
+When omitted while
+.Fl U
+and
+.Fl G
+are provided, supplementary groups are cleared.
+.El
+.Pp
+When credential drop options are configured, the supervisor applies them in
+the order
+.Xr setgroups 2 ,
+.Xr setgid 2 ,
+then
+.Xr setuid 2
+after entering the cell root and kernel cell membership.
+.Pp
+The background supervisor process is shown in process listings as
+.Dq cellctl supervise cell=<name> cid=<id>
+to distinguish it from one-shot supervise invocations.
+.It Cm destroy Ar cell-id | name
+Destroy a cell selected by
+.Ar cell-id
+or
+.Ar name
+that has no remaining processes.
+.It Cm exec Ar cell-id | name Op command Op Ar args ...
+Enter a running cell selected by
+.Ar cell-id
+or
+.Ar name
+using the root stored in kernel cell metadata and execute
+.Ar command .
+If no command is provided, an interactive shell is started.
+.It Cm list Op Fl T Op Fl H
+List active cell ids, process counts, configured cell names, ages, roots, and
+supervise rlimits
+.Pq nofile, as, core .
+Age is emitted in seconds since cell creation.
+With
+.Fl T ,
+emit stable tab-separated output with columns:
+.Dq CID NAME REFS PROCS AGE ROOT NOFILE AS CORE .
+With
+.Fl H ,
+omit the TSV header line
+.Pq requires .Fl T .
+.It Cm stats Op Fl P Op Fl v Op Fl h Op Fl T Op Fl H
+Show current cell snapshot metrics from the kernel sampler
+.Pq CPU ticks over 1s and rolling 10s windows, process count, reference count, virtual memory size, and cell age in seconds .
+By default, output is a compact human-readable table.
+All exported values are snapshot gauges.
+In particular,
+.Dq CPU1S
+is the per-second CPU tick delta over the latest sampling window, and
+.Dq CPU10S
+is the rolling 10-second average of that value.
+With
+.Fl v ,
+show an extended table that includes root path and reference count.
+With
+.Fl T ,
+emit stable tab-separated output with columns:
+.Dq CID NAME CPU1S CPU10S PROCS REFS MEMORY AGE ROOT .
+With
+.Fl H ,
+omit the TSV header line
+.Pq requires .Fl T .
+The
+.Fl T
+option is mutually exclusive with
+.Fl P ,
+.Fl v ,
+and
+.Fl h .
+With
+.Fl P ,
+output Prometheus-compatible gauge samples per cell.
+This includes per-cell age as
+.Dq cell_age_seconds .
+With
+.Fl h ,
+prepend an HTTP response header suitable for running
+.Cm stats Fl P
+behind
+.Xr inetd 8
+.Pq e.g. status line plus text/plain content type .
+The
+.Fl h
+option requires
+.Fl P .
+.El
+.Sh SEE ALSO
+.Xr chroot 2 ,
+.Xr secmodel 9 ,
+.Xr secmodel_cell 9 ,
+.Xr sysctl 8
+.Sh HISTORY
+The
+.Nm
+utility first appeared in an unofficial patch set for
+.Nx
+11.0 .
+.Sh AUTHORS
+.An Matthias Petermann Aq Mt mp@petermann-digital.de
